Boil a large #pot{} of salted @water{to taste} with @salt{to taste} for the @rice{150%g}.

Once boiling, add the rice and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}. Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pot. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Chop the @grilling cheese{200%g} into 2cm chunks and pop them into a #bowl{} of water to soak.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}%halved, peeled and chopped into small pieces}.

Drain the @sweet corn{1%pack} in a sieve.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with @butter{2%tbsp} (double for 4p). Remove the cheese from its bowl onto some #kitchen paper{}.

Once hot, add the cheese to the pan. Fry until golden all over, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn every ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the cheese is golden, transfer to a bowl then return your pan to medium-high heat.

Add the onion to the remaining butter in the pan and fry until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the sweet corn along with the @passata{1%pack} and @water{50%ml} (double for 4p). Simmer for ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir in the golden fried cheese and half the @creme fraiche{125%g} and allow to warm through. Add a splash of water if required.

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Season the sauce to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}.

Serve the sweet corn butter masala alongside the fluffy rice.

Garnish with @cashews{20%g}, coriander and a dollop of remaining creme fraiche.